\begin_layout Problem
Find 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 smooth functions 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ U_{i}(x,t)\right\} _{i=1}^{m}$
\end_inset

 satisfying the PDE system
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left(\pdv{t}+\Matrix{A(U)}\pdv{x}\right)\ket{U}=\ket{0}\label{eq:QuasilinearHyperbolicSystem1d}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and the smooth IC system 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:SmoothInitialWaveSystem"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, in which 
\begin_inset Formula $\Matrix{A(U)}$
\end_inset

 is a matrix function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like a linear system, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Matrix{A(U)}$
\end_inset

 can be diagonalized at any arbitrary point 
\begin_inset Formula $(U_{1},\dots,U_{m})$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\Matrix{A(U)} & =\Matrix{R(U)}\Matrix{\lambda(U)}\Matrix{R(U)}^{-1}\\
 & =\Matrix{L(U)}^{-1}\Matrix{\lambda(U)}\Matrix{L(U)}
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

However, PDE system 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:QuasilinearHyperbolicSystem1d"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 cannot be fully decoupled in general.
 We can at most have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\Matrix{L(U)}\pdv{t}+\Matrix{\lambda(U)}\Matrix{L(U)}\pdv{x}\right)\ket{U}=\ket{0}
\]

\end_inset

each row of which is a 
\noun on
characteristic compatibility condition
\noun default

\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
characteristic!~ compatibility condition
\end_layout

\end_inset

, which can be written as a PDE
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mel**{L_{i}(U)}{\pdv{t}+\lambda_{i}(U)\pdv{x}}{U}=0\qquad i=1,\dots,m\label{eq:CharacteristicCompatibilityCondition}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

or an ODE
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\ip{L_{i}(U)}{\left(\dv{t}\right)_{i}{U}}=0\qquad i=1,\dots,m
\]

\end_inset

by defining a differential operator
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\dv{t}\right)_{i}:=\pdv{t}+\lambda_{i}(U)\pdv{x}
\]

\end_inset

along the characteristic curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{x}{t}=\lambda_{i}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In contrast to the linear case, 
\begin_inset Formula $\bra{L_{i}(U)}$
\end_inset

 cannot be exchanged with the differential operator, so the characteristic
 compatibility condition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:CharacteristicCompatibilityCondition"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 cannot be decoupled into 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 independent PDEs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
For each 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, the function 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}(U_{1},\dots,U_{m})$
\end_inset

 defines a scalar field in the 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

-space, which is called the 
\noun on

\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

th characteristic field
\noun default
.
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
characteristic!~ field
\end_layout

\end_inset

 A characteristic field is categorized as 
\noun on
genuinely nonlinear
\noun default

\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
characteristic!~ field!genuinely nonlinear ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

